# Costing app — core

- **Next.js**: This repo may differ from public Next.js docs. Before Route Handlers, `next.config`, or App Router APIs, read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` for this version. Heed deprecations.
- **Scope**: Change only what the task requires. No drive-by refactors, no unrelated UI restyling.
- **Secrets**: Never commit API keys, connection strings, or `.env*`. Client code must not embed secrets.
- **Money / numbers**: Prefer explicit rounding where totals matter. Costing logic belongs in `lib/calculations/*`, `lib/ahu-segment-costing.ts`, `lib/project-rollup.ts` — not scattered in UI.
- **Source of truth**: Domain rules live in code + Prisma schema. Agent rules and skills **guide** behavior; they do not replace reading the actual files.
- **SaaS readiness**: When adding auth or multi-tenancy, every data access must eventually be scoped by tenant — see `docs/PRODUCTION-HARNESS.md`.
